== Defining Severe Pediatric ME/CFS
<sec:ped-severe-definition>

Severe pediatric ME/CFS is defined by functional impairment that prevents normal school attendance and requires substantial caregiver support for daily activities. Unlike adult severity metrics that emphasize work capacity, pediatric severity must be assessed through the lens of age-appropriate functioning, including school participation, extracurricular activities, and peer socialization @Rowe2017pediatric.

